  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "ISO 9660 images start with 16 empty 2048-byte sectors (the system area, bytes 0-32767) before the first Volume Descriptor at sector 16 (offset 32768). The system area can contain bootable code (El Torito) or hidden data. Multiple volume descriptor types may follow; the Volume Descriptor Set Terminator (type 255) signals the end of the VD set.",
    "knownVulnerabilities": [],
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Inspect the system area (bytes 0–32767) for bootable code or hidden content not part of the ISO 9660 structure",
      "Check volumeDescriptorType: 0=Boot Record, 1=PVD, 2=Supplementary (Joliet), 255=Terminator",
      "Verify the Volume Descriptor Set Terminator is present to confirm a well-formed VD sequence",
      "Examine the path table and directory records for entries with unusual names or abnormal offsets"
